 <title ixia_locid="1">Remote Logging Requirements</title>
 <shortdesc ixia_locid="2">Titanium Server supports continuously streaming detailed system logs from all hosts to a
  remote log server for centralized review and analysis.</shortdesc>
 <prolog>
  <author ixia_locid="3">Craig Griffin</author>
 </prolog>
 <conbody>
  <p ixia_locid="4">When centralized logging is enabled, logs written to the <filepath ixia_locid="5">/var/log</filepath> directory on each host are also sent to a remote log server.
   Each host sends logs through the active controller to a remote log server over the OAM network
   using either TCP or UDP. For added security, a TLS connection can be configured.</p>
  <p ixia_locid="6">The following figure shows how Remote Logging works.</p>
  <fig id="fig_f2y_nbl_wx" ixia_locid="7">
   
   <image href="xwl1478551192216.image" id="image_ll4_fcl_wx" ixia_locid="9">
    <alt ixia_locid="10">Remote Logging Feature</alt>
   </image>
  </fig>
